    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fastenings for French doors or casement windows that consist of sliding rods that engage with strikes or plates at the top or bottom of the frame of the portal. The rod is controlled by a handle that retracts the upper and lower parts of the bolt from the frame. </Note_Text>
